column2: Virginia's 2-2-2 from X Offense Master Class
column3:
Virginia’s 2-2-2 from X played an extensive role in their 2019 National Championship run. Virginia used it to score: the game-winning goal in overtime vs Syracuse in the regular season, the game-winning goal in overtime vs Maryland in the quarterfinals, the game-tying and game-winning goals vs Duke in the Semi-Finals, and 5 of 13 goals in the National Championship vs Yale.

The keys to Virginia’s 2-2-2 from X are:

Simplicity - It’s simple enough to allow players to alternate between positions.

Easy Reads - Defensive decisions create a cascade of reads that are easy to see and teach.

Spacing - The spacing makes defensive decisions difficult and allows players to freelance easily if the prescribed looks aren’t there.

This Master Class includes the Virginia 2-2-2 From X POWLAX Playbook PDF.

Upon completing the quiz with an 80% score, you will receive a POWLAX Certificate of Completion.

column2: Twist Man Up Play Master Class
column3:
Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the Twist Man Up Play! This simple yet efficient play can be used by teams of all levels, from 6th grade to varsity. The Twist Man Up Play is designed to allow players to read the play rather than look for specific looks, making it a foundational element of any team's game plan. Our experienced instructor, Patrick, will guide you through the key principles and tactics of the Twist Man Up Play, providing you with the knowledge and skills you need to implement it effectively. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will help you take your team's man-up offense to the next level. Don't miss this opportunity to learn from the best – sign up now!

This Master Class includes the Twist Man Up Play POWLAX Playbook PDF.

Earn the Twist Man Up Play Certificate of Completion by passing the quiz with a score of 80% or higher.

column2: Ohio State Pairs Motion Offense Master Class
column3:
Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the Ohio State Pairs Offense! This course will take you through the offensive system that Ohio State used to crush Denver in 2017 on their way to a National Championship appearance. The pairs offense has gained popularity with the widespread adoption of 2 Man Game principles and is known for being extremely simple and requiring players to be diligent and make great decisions. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will provide you with the knowledge and skills you need to successfully implement the Ohio State Pairs Offense in your team's game plan. This Master Class includes the Ohio State Pairs POWLAX Playbook PDF.

column2: Executing and Defending Two-Man Games in Lacrosse Master Class
column3:
Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the 2 Man Game! This comprehensive course will teach you about the various tactics and strategies used by two players with the goal of getting one of them open and in on goal. The 2 Man Game has become a staple of collegiate lacrosse, with every team that made the NCAA Tournament in 2019 using it as a primary attacking principle within their offense. In this course, you will learn about the perfect Pick and a range of other options that players have as they move into and out of the traditional "Pick and Roll" scenario. Our experienced instructor, Patrick, will guide you through the key principles and tactics of the 2 Man Game, providing you with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will help you take your team's offense to the next level. Don't miss this opportunity to learn from the best – sign up now!

This Master Class includes the "Executing and Defending 2 Man Games Playbook PDF."

This Master Class includes many lessons with their own individual quizzes.

Led by, 2019 Tewaaraton Award Finalist and record-setting distributor Grant Ament (1) and sniper Mac O’Keefe (3), Penn State scored 17.94 goals per game and had the #1 offense in 2019. Although the performance of Ament and O’Keefe drew the headlines, neither would have achieved nearly as much without the exceptional play of Dylan Foulds (14), Nick Spillane (13), Jack Kelly (25), TJ Malone (7), and a few others. Anytime the defense gave Ament or O’Keefe too much room they would get burned. When the defense adjusted to help cover Ament or O’Keefe the others would capitalize. The six players were like piranhas, combining to be nearly unstoppable.

This Master Class will walk you through the 3 phases of the Penn State Offense: The 3 High Pairs Offense, 1-4-1 Wing Pairs Offense, and the Picks Behind Offense.

This Master Class includes the Penn State Offense Playbook PDF

Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the 21-12 offensive concept! This innovative course will teach you a revolutionary approach to offense that combines four traditional sets – 2-2-2, 2-3-1, 1-3-2, and Open – into a single, easy-to-understand system. The 21-12 concept is perfect for coaches looking to quickly train and modify their players' skills using small-sided 3 Man games and motions. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will provide you with the knowledge and tools you need to take your team's offensive game to the next level. Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the Near Man Defense! This course will cover a man-to-man defense strategy that combines elements from both crease and adjacent slide defenses. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse player or coach, this course will provide you with the knowledge and skills you need to effectively implement the Near Man Defense in game situations. column2: Parker Hawks Youth Lacrosse Coaching Master Class
column3:
This comprehensive Master Class is designed for coaches at all levels. This program is a complete system to understand and teach youth lacrosse effectively. Whether you're a seasoned coach or a parent stepping into the role, this Master Class offers a one-stop solution for all your coaching needs by providing you with the mental scaffolding to integrate all of your lacrosse coaching knowledge.

The Parker Hawks Youth Lacrosse Coaching Master class includes additional material, not found in the Youth Lacrosse Coaching Master Class. Including the Executing and Defending 2 Man Games Series, 4 Man Wheel Man Up Offenses, and 22 Quick Man Up Set Play.

As a member of this Master Class you have access to all of the printable Playbook PDFs, which are found in the materials section of each lesson. If you'd like a playbook pdf for a video that is not included in this Master Class, navigate using the Powlax.com menu to the video and click the red PDF link at the bottom of the page. You must be logged in to download the PDF.

column2: 1-4-1 Shifted Triangles Motion Offense Master Class
column3: Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the 1-4-1 Shifted Triangles Motion Offense! This lacrosse strategy involves a dynamic 141 offense derived from the traditional 2112 motion offense, focusing on player movement, positioning, and coordinated dodging to create scoring opportunities. It emphasizes a push-pull motion for ball handlers, strategic positioning for off-ball players, and quick adaptation to defensive actions to maintain offensive advantage and exploit weaknesses. Our experienced instructors will guide you through every aspect of the 1-4-1 Shifted Triangles Motion Offense, from its key principles to its tactical implementation. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will provide the knowledge and skills you need to run the 1-4-1 Shifted Triangles Motion Offense! Don't miss this opportunity to learn from the best and take your team's power play to the next level – sign up now!
column9: 1-4-1 Double Mumbo to Weave Set Play

column2: 1-4-1 Double Mumbo to Weave Set Play Master Class
column3: Welcome to our lacrosse master class on the 1-4-1 Double Mumbo to Weave Set Play! The lacrosse strategy involves executing the 141 double Mumbo that everyone loves but adds a weave motion over the top, using coordinated picks and player movements to disorient the defense and create multiple scoring opportunities. This approach emphasizes teamwork, timing, and precise execution to exploit defensive weaknesses and generate advantageous situations for attackers. Our experienced instructors will guide you through every aspect of the 1-4-1 Double Mumbo to Weave Set Play, from its key principles to its tactical implementation. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced lacrosse coach, this course will provide the knowledge and skills you need to run the 1-4-1 Double Mumbo to Weave Set Play! Don't miss this opportunity to learn from the best and take your team's power play to the next level – sign up now!

column3:
Gain a quick yet comprehensive overview of lacrosse with our concise master class designed for parents. In this course, you'll discover:

  • What Is Lacrosse?
    A brief introduction to the game's history, rules, and unique appeal.

  • Choosing the Right Stick:
    Tips and guidance on selecting the perfect lacrosse stick for your young athlete.

  • Comparisons to Other Sports:
    Insights into how lacrosse stacks up against more familiar sports.

  • Fundamentals Master Classes:
    Essential skills and techniques to help you understand the game’s core elements.

Equip yourself with the basics to confidently support your child's lacrosse journey!
